I felt a shamed and embarrassed because there was no reason why I should've been told to leave, especially the way he did. This is one of my favorite Italian places to eat in the city. Homemade pasta coupled with an infrequently alternating menu means that this is a reliable and absolutely delicious place to bring my family or any out-of-town guests. The strozzapreti alla norcina is a family favorite, as is their bolognese. The wood fired pizzas are a nice size to share at the table or to eat individually, and their staff is always welcoming and playing with my baby daughter. My two qualms are that there seems to be no air conditioning (which honestly just lends to the replication of an Italian atmosphere), and that the non-alcoholic drink menu is extremely limited. However, neither of these things were enough to keep me away in the dead heat of August when I was 9 months pregnant, because their food is that good. Love this place, and very highly recommend if you want actual delicious Italian fare.
